  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0 \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0d9a\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A Chinese company to salvage the Express Pearl ship",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The first interim report on the calculation and preparation of the environmental damage caused to the coastline and coastline due to the MV Express Pearl container ship which sank in Sri Lankan waters on May 20 last year while carrying goods under the Singapore flag, is an Australian expertise in ship accident compensation. Ms. Darshanee Lahadapura, Chairperson of the Marine Environment Protection Authority, said that the law has been sent to the law firm.",
        "She also mentioned that after receiving the instructions from that institution, further legal steps will be taken together with the Attorney General's Department.",
        "She also said that the Treasury has received 1.3 billion rupees from the ship's insurance company for cleaning up the beach by removing the plastic and waste released from the sinking of the ship.",
        "She said that the cabinet paper submitted requesting an amount of 903,857,293 rupees from the Treasury to settle the related payment activities has been approved so far.",
        "Also, the chairman of the Maritime Environment Protection Authority said that the company that owns the ship has entrusted the recovery of the sunken Express Pearl ship to a Chinese company.",
        "However, due to the rough seas during the Warakan, the salvage operations have been temporarily halted and the operations will be resumed in November this year, she said.",
        "The MV Express Pearl container ship, which was carrying goods under the flag of Singapore, caught fire on 20th May last year while anchored 9 nautical miles away from Colombo port and sank on 02nd June.",
        "The fire was caused by the nitric acid stored in the ship and due to an explosion before the ship sank, some of the 1486 containers in it fell into the sea.",
        "The 746 km sea area from Mannar to Hambantota Kirinda was completely polluted by the mixing of the chemicals and plastic beads in these containers with the sea water.",
        "The cleaning of the beach contaminated by waste from the ship MV Express Pearl has been carried out since May 20 last year. At present, the cleaning activities are taking place at 2723 places, covering a distance of 746 km."
      ],
